/blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Study after study has shown that if you take a group of random people and split them into 2-3 groups randomly they will quickly break into and &quot;us and them&quot; mentality.<br>
<br>
This is shown over and over and over in EQ where class lines are the &quot;us and them&quot;.  I am sure that if I had chosen a mage I would be annoyed that wizards got all the portability, nuking, snaring etc...without being asked for mod rods and focus items all the time.<br>
<br>
I play a wizard so I am annoyed that mages can nuke almost as hard as us (there is that word again) and have pets that are fantastic.<br>
<br>
I imagine druids hate us both, and I am convinced every necro hates everyone.<br>
<br>
I decided a while ago I would be happy whenever a friend of mine won something that I also wanted.  And would be happy when other classes get powers and abilities...because I am secure in the fact that my class still kicks ass.<br>
<br>
Garrath Moore<br>
Sorceror <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=joklun>Joklun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/2/03 9:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> who cares</span><hr size=1> &quot;For example, another thread in this forum complains that magicians want concussion, and this is just another foolish want in a long list of mage complaints, as if mages were no better than druids.&quot;<br>
<br>
Mage are no better than druids, because their isnt mages and druids, its all &quot;people&quot;. I am getting tired of this kind of attitude in EQ, people that think their class make them better than others.<br>
<br>
I had friends from all classes in EQ, and I put some guys on ignore from all classes too.<br>
<br>
I dont have enough time to read all these boards fully, even less time to do writing of my own here, but if guys truly beleive that you or your(any) class is better than another for whats writen on these boards, then I am happy I cant read it all, cause what I miss out much my nonsense indeed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/03 1:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Now I say son, what YOU'RE looking for is a CHICKEN!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>as if mages were no better than druids<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->In my best Foghorn Leghorn: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;That's a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">joke</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, son, yah supposed to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">laugh</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->!<br>
<br>
Nice boy, but about as bright as inkwell.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
For some time, the oldest major druid board was known for its insistant petitions for dramatic improvements to the druid class, while at the same time many other classes felt strongly that druid abilities were both broad and lacked any significant weakness, so that dramatic improvements should not be forthcoming.  Consider that druids are hard nuking healers with great utility, it is easy to see how wizards in particular are upset by druid demands, especially considering that the two classes share the same solo method, kiting, and therefore fight over the same spawns.<br>
<br>
